snippet.textDisplay: I just wanted to say: NO ONE eats unripe jackfruit plain like that. NO ONE. We eat it as a meat substitute, so it will mimic things like pulled pork, but in order to do that, we roast and marinate it in BBQ sauce. I’ve also had jackfruit “chicken” sandwiches where it has been marinated for hours, roasted and then served with vegan mayonnaise in a sandwich. Seriously. Why serve it plain like that?
